  "prompt": "I stopped talking to girl completely whom I love after I got to know that she got engaged to a different guy. Now her marriage has been called off and I want to ask her out. How do I do it?",
  "response": "Here are some thoughtful steps to approach this situation:\n\n1. Reflect first\n- Be sure your feelings are genuine and not just a reaction to her being single again\n- Consider why the marriage was called off and if there are underlying issues\n\n2. Rebuild communication gradually\n- Start with casual, friendly messages\n- Don't immediately jump into romantic intentions\n- Be respectful and understanding\n\n3. When reconnecting\n- Be honest about your past feelings\n- Apologize if you completely cut her off earlier\n- Show genuine care and interest in her current situation\n\n4. Take it slow\n- Don't rush into asking her out immediately\n- Rebuild trust and friendship first\n- Understand her emotional state after a broken engagement\n\n5. When you feel the time is right\n- Have an honest conversation about your feelings\n- Be prepared that she might not be interested\n- Respect her decision whatever it may be\n\n6. Important considerations\n- Give her space and time to heal\n- Don't seem opportunistic\n- Be patient and understanding\n\nCommunication, respect, and emotional maturity are key in this situation. Approach her with genuine care and be prepared for any outcome.",
